elements.name: entryDateElectionCode
elements.description:
A code representing the source of the Elected Entry Date. Valid codes are:

W = Weekly Entry (Entry type 06, only)

Code “W” is only reported on an entry type 06 when the transaction is being used to submit a Weekly Entry.

elements.name: electedEntryDate
elements.description:
Enter a numeric date in MMDDYY (month, day, year) format.

The date submitted in this field will be used as the Date of Entry for Entry Summary and duty calculation purposes.

For entry type 06, and an Entry Date Election Code = “W” (Weekly Entry), this represents the date of the first day of the Zone Week.

elements.name: locationOfGoodsFirms
elements.description: FIRMS code of the location where the 4 cargo is currently stored.

elements.name: electedExamSiteFirms
elements.description:
Filer’s preferred Centralized Examination Station (CES) location.

For use when CBP determines that a required Intensive Examination is to be conducted at a Centralized Examination Station (CES).

As per CD 3550-29, if there is more than one CES in the port of entry, the broker/filer specifies which CES location they wish used for the examination.

If there is only one CES in the port of entry, no FIRMS Code needs to be submitted for this data element.

This data element should be Space Filled if no FIRMS Code is being submitted.

elements.name: conveyanceNameOrFtzId
elements.description:
Name of the Conveyance.

Legacy 7 Character Zone ID
FTZ ID = 3 numeric
Sub zone/GP ID = 2 alpha-numeric
Site ID = 2 alpha-numeric

Updated ACE 9 Character Zone ID
FTZ ID = 3 numeric
Sub zone/GP ID = 3 alpha-numeric
Site ID = 3 alpha-numeric

For entry type 06, list the Foreign Trade ZoneID. The data must be submitted in the format specified in Note 6*.

*NOTE: Please refer to Note 6 below for proper format of the FTZ ID.
[Note: This is not the same format that is used on the e214 FTZ Admission.]

elements.name: voyageFlightTripManifestNumber
elements.description: The voyage/flight/trip number of the 7 importing carrier.

elements.name: generalOrderGONumber
elements.description: The G.O. Number if the cargo has been placed in General Order.

elements.name: cbpBondedWarehouseFirms
elements.description: FIRMS code of the CBP Bonded 2 Warehouse where cargo is to be entered. (Entry Types 21 and 22 only)

elements.name: originatingWarehouseEntryFilerCode
elements.description:
Filer Code of the originating warehouse entry that the merchandise is coming from. The Originating entry listed must be entry type 21 or 22 only.

The Entry Filer Code occupies the first three positions of an entry number.

elements.name: originatingWarehouseEntryNumber
elements.description:
Originating warehouse entry number that the merchandise is coming from. The Originating entry listed must be entry type 21 or 22 only.

Unique identifying number assigned to the Entry by the Filer. For additional information on valid entry number formats, refer to Appendix B of the ACE CATAIR Chapters publication.

elements.name: immediateDeliveryIndicator
elements.description: Space fill. Not currently in use.
